rComments: Really sweet person but requires that you know a lot of information. Tests on specific phrases/terms - if you don't write exactly what she's looking for, you won't get points. Good lecturer, clearly loves neurochemistry, great to talk to. Loved her as a professor. Just be prepared to read the textbook and study hard!
If you're interested in neuroscience and want a down-to-earth prof who will teach you things in dynamic ways, take De Rosa's class. She's an absolute gem and I was never bored in neuro chemistry!
Like all professors at U of T, she is good. She tried to make the material come to life. Unfortunately, I think the exams were confusing - perhaps that is why I did so badly.
Really nice, always happy to answer questions. Always asks for feedback and changes lectures accordingly. Tests required very specific knowledge.
